üì± Core Platforms
 * Node.js - Async non-blocking event-driven JavaScript runtime built on Chrome's V8.
 * React 18 - The library for web and native user interfaces.
 * Cross-Platform - Fully responsive design compatible with macOS, Windows, and Linux browsers.
 Programming Languages
 * JavaScript - The primary language for the full-stack implementation.
 * TypeScript - Optional static typing for the core review logic.
 * Markdown - Used for generating high-quality documentation and review reports.
Front-End Architecture
 * Tailwind CSS - Utility-first CSS framework for rapid, modern UI development.
 * Lucide Icons - Beautiful & consistent icons for the dashboard.
 * Framer Motion - Production-ready motion library for React transitions.
 * Axios - Promise-based HTTP client for seamless API communication. 
Back-End Infrastructure
 * Express - Minimalist web framework for the Node.js API layer.
 * Cors - Middleware to enable secure cross-origin resource sharing.
 * Dotenv - Secure environment variable management for API keys.
 * Helmet - Express middleware to help secure your app by setting various HTTP headers.
Artificial Intelligence
 * Gemini/Grok API - Large Language Models used for deep semantic code analysis.
 * Prompt Engineering - Curated system instructions for high-accuracy bug detection.
 * Generative AI - Framework for building intelligent, context-aware code suggestions.
üõ†Ô∏è Development Environment
 * GitHub Actions - CI/CD pipelines for automated testing and deployment.
 * Concurrently - Orchestration tool to run frontend and backend in a single terminal.
 * ESLint - Plug-and-play linting for maintaining code consistency.
 * Prettier - Opinionated code formatter for standardized styling.
 Security & Testing
 * Jest - Delightful JavaScript Testing Framework with a focus on simplicity.
 * Supertest - High-level abstraction for testing HTTP endpoints.
 * Security Scanning - Automated dependency vulnerability checks.
 Special Thanks
Our ecosystem is supported by the innovation of the open-source community:
 * Nitric - Effortless backends and infrastructure.
 * Wispr Flow - Staying in the flow with voice-to-code.
 * Depot - Blazing fast remote container builds.


Contribution Guide
Contributions are what make the open-source community such an amazing place to learn, inspire, and create.
 * Fork the Project
 * Create your Feature Branch (git checkout -b feature/AmazingFeature)
 * Commit your Changes (git commit -m 'Add some AmazingFeature')
 * Push to the Branch (git push origin feature/AmazingFeature)
 * Open a Pull Request
